result.execSummary:
The defendant Latisha M Johnson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery to Law Enforcement Officers, Fire Fighters or Commission Wardens [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "H" Felony], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.20(2).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Penalty-Theft if Value <=$2500, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Criminal Trespass to Dwelling [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Latisha M Johnson in court with attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor.  Defendant Latisha M Johnson in custody.  Michael Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

SPEEDY JURY TRIAL previously scheduled for 08-11-2014 at 09:00am is removed from Court's Calendar.

-  AMENDED INFORMATION FILED.
COUNT 1 AMENDED to Battery To  A Law Enforcement Officer, contrary to 940.20(2), 939.30(3)(h), Wisconsin Stats, a CLASS H FELONY.

COUNT 2 AMENDED to Theft (Value Not Exceeding $2,500), contrary to 943.20(1)(a) and (3)(a), Wisconsin Stats, a CLASS A MISDEMEANOR.

COUNT 3 AMENDED to Criminal Trespass To Dwelling, contrary to 943.14, 939.51(3)(a), Wisconsin Stats, a CLASS A MISDEMEANOR.

AS TO AMENDED COUNTS, 1,2, and 3, Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised she is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised she is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible. 


Sentencing proceeds. No corrections made to PSI report. Statements made by the State, defense counsel and defendant. Additional statements made by: Detective Eileen W.

AS TO COUNT 1
Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 3 YEARS and 6 MONTHS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 1YEAR and 6 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS. Credit given for 64 days time served if revoked.  25% of prison funds, collected by Department of Corrections, to go toward all court ordered monetary obligations, with restitution having first priority, and all other monetary obligations thereafter, if revoked.
.
COURT STAYS sentence and places defendant on PROBATION for 3 YEARS.
-
Court orders defendant to serve 7 MONTHS CONDITION TIME IN THE HOUSE OF CORRECTION, with HUBER RELEASE PRIVILEGES FOR DAY REPORTING CENTER AFTER SERVING 3 MONTHS.  
-
AS TO COUNT 2
Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT 1. Credit for 0 days time served. COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 years, CONCURRENT TO COUNT 1.

AS TO COUNT 3
Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT 1 and CONCURRENT TO COUNT 2. Credit for 0 days time served. COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 years, CONCURRENT TO COUNTS 1 and 2.

.
